Hey @gregor  I tried to compile a smart contract with OffchainState but I got a bunch of errors around the OffchainState config I made, can you check it?

```
node_modules/o1js/dist/node/lib/mina/actions/offchain-state.d.ts:103:32 - error TS1139: Type parameter declaration expected.

103 declare function OffchainState<const Config extends {
                                   ~~~~~
...
Found 15 errors in the same file, starting at: node_modules/o1js/dist/node/lib/mina/actions/offchain-state.d.ts:103

``` 

I had the following config in my main Smart Contract 
```

const { OffchainState, OffchainStateCommitments } = Experimental;

export const offchainState = OffchainState({
  prices: OffchainState.Map(Field, Field),
});
export class PriceProof extends offchainState.Proof {}
```
And the state is as follow 
```
 @state(OffchainStateCommitments) offchainState = State(
    OffchainStateCommitments.empty()
  );
```
